        if isinstance(other, MyClass):
            return self.value == other.value
        return False
```

In this case, attempting to use an instance of `MyClass` as a dictionary key or set element will raise a `TypeError`.

### Conclusion

If you want your instances to be hashable and usable as dictionary keys or set elements, implement both `__eq__` and `__hash__` methods. If not, simply implement `__eq__` without `__hash__` to prevent their use as dictionary keys or set elements.
